["s: The Court of Appeals, Reyna, Circuit Judge, held that:

[1] under Tenth Circuit law, plaintiff acted vexatiously in continuing to litigate;

[2] Under Tenth Circuit law, district court had authority to strike plaintiff's objection to award of attorneys' fees;

[3] district court's failure to consider plaintiff's argument in his objection to award of attorneys' fees did not constitute
denial of due process;

[4] district court had jurisdiction to enter order awarding sanctions; and

[5] plaintiff's appeal was frivolous.

Affirmed; motions for sanctions granted.

"]

['s: The Court of Appeals, Taranto, Circuit Judge, held that:

[1] government was entitled to postjudgment interest;

[2] government forfeited right to prejudgment interest;

[3] suspension of liquidation was not invalidated;

[4] surety was not discharged from bond obligations; and

[5] bonds were valid and enforceable.

